# KGD Account Tracker — V1 Setup & Launch Guide

## ✅ What's Built

All V1 features are complete and code-ready:

| Feature | Status |
|---|---|
| Auth (login/session/roles) | ✅ |
| Customer list, create, edit, detail | ✅ |
| Contact management per customer | ✅ |
| Customer ledger (invoices + payments timeline) | ✅ |
| Products (plates & sheets), create/edit | ✅ |
| Invoice creation (multi-item, manual rates) | ✅ |
| Invoice list, detail, cancel | ✅ |
| Invoice print view (auto-opens print dialog) | ✅ |
| Payment recording with invoice allocation | ✅ |
| Payments list | ✅ |
| Dashboard (stats, outstanding balances, recent activity) | ✅ |
| Inventory (stock tracking, manual movements) | ✅ |
| Audit log (admin-only) | ✅ |

---

## 🚀 Steps to Run Locally

### 1. Setup PostgreSQL Database

Create a database named `kgd_tracker` (or any name):

```sql
CREATE DATABASE kgd_tracker;
```

### 2. Update [.env](file:///c:/Users/smummare/OneDrive%20-%20Arizona%20State%20University/From%20Lumin%20-%20sort%20them/Documents/projects/KGD_ACCOUNT_TRACKING/kgd-app/.env)

Edit [kgd-app/.env](file:///c:/Users/smummare/OneDrive%20-%20Arizona%20State%20University/From%20Lumin%20-%20sort%20them/Documents/projects/KGD_ACCOUNT_TRACKING/kgd-app/.env):

```env
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://YOUR_USER:YOUR_PASSWORD@localhost:5432/kgd_tracker"
NEXTAUTH_SECRET="change-this-in-production-use-a-real-random-secret"
NEXTAUTH_URL="http://localhost:3000"
```

### 3. Run Database Migrations

```bash
cd kgd-app
npx prisma migrate dev --name init
```

This creates all tables from the schema.

### 4. Seed Initial Data

```bash
npm run db:seed
```

This creates:
- **Admin user**: `admin@kgd.com` / `admin123`
- **Staff user**: `staff@kgd.com` / `staff123`
- Sample products and inventory items

### 5. Start the App

```bash
npm run dev
```

Open [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000) and login.

